Well located next to the shopping area, with Lidl, Radio Popular, Leroy Merlin, Continente, Norauto, and Bombas Prio, restaurants, close to the A5 Lisboa/Cascais, Marginal, C: P. Carcavelos and Carcavelos beach. Jardim Quinta da Alagoa, once belonged to the Company of Jesus, was the Carcavelos wine production farm, but today it is a green nucleus remaining from recent urban growth processes, remaining as a fundamental collective equipment of the parish of Carcavelos. From the past it preserves on the edge, traces of the original forest, flowerbeds in boxwood topiary next to the ruins of the old buildings, as well as structural elements of the farm, namely hydraulic parts for capturing groundwater and storage and conduction to the surface. The lagoon that gives it its name is, even today, fed in the same way, by capturing groundwater. Widely sought after by the local population, it is a space for informal use where active and passive recreation is possible on the wide lawns, on the two playgrounds, on the tennis courts, in the surroundings of the lagoon and even in a more nostalgic way next to the most architectural elements. old.

It also has a covered parking space and a storage room. Mark your visit User License nº 200 in.

T3 in Graça, Refurbished, in good condition. 3 bedrooms, one of which could be a living room, kitchen with hob and extractor fan, sunroom and balcony. Central with access to various transport, trade and services. Accessible parking, close to car park. Housing permit, prior to 1951. Great for Students or young people starting out life and choose to live in the center of the Capital. The proximity to transport is an asset. Thanks to a quiet area with several tourist spots, good access on foot.
